The bread and butter of Twitter is getting more followers, but to get more followers you ultimately need to get more retweets.

A new study has looked into the science behind what makes a tweet popular and therefore more likely to be shared, and has discovered it may be as simple as just adding a photo.

Dan Zarrella, HubSpot's social-media scientist, discovered that tweets including photos, and in particular photos hosted by Twitter's own picture service, are 94 per cent more likely to be shared.

