Instagram was 64 per cent less likely to be shared, while Facebook was 47 per cent. Twitpic came out in second place with a retweet rate 64 per cent more likely.

Zarella said: 'Using a dataset of 482,865 randomly selected tweets, I found that using Twitter's native image uploading system greatly improved the odds of a tweet being retweeted.

'Twitpic had a less powerful, but still positive effect, while Facebook and Instagram image links had negative effects.'

